questions.explanation:
Find the lowest common denominator, which is $(x - 2)(x + 3)$. Rewrite the fractions:\frac{5(x + 3) - 3(x - 2)}{(x - 2)(x + 3)}$. Expand the terms in the numerator:$5x + 15 - 3x + 6$. Group like terms together to simplify:$2x + 21$. This gives the final fraction as$\frac{2x + 21}{(x - 2)(x + 3)}

$$.

**Common mistake:** Examiners note that students often fail to distribute the negative sign properly when expanding $-3(x - 2)$, writing $-6$ instead of $+6$.
